        <div class="col-xs-10 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          My name is Hinh Martin Nguyen.  Just Martin for non-Vietnamese friends.  As Steve Jobs recommended, "Your work is going to fill a large part of your life, and the only way to be truly satisfied is to do what you believe is great work. And the only way to do great work is to love what you do. If you haven't found it yet, keep looking. Don't settle. As with all matters of the heart, you'll know when you find it."  It took me a long time, but I believe that I have finally found my work passion that Steve Jobs eloquently spoke of.  This passion is technology and having the opportunity to solve problems using my knowledge, creativity, and engineering skills.<br><br>

          Here is a brief istory of how I got to this point in my life.  After graduating from Texas A&M University with a Bachelor of Science degree in engineering, I was unsure wither working as an engineer was my calling.  I was always interested in the cross-road between business and technology, especially the Internet, which was an exploding phenomenon at the time.  Luckly, my brother, Mark, who also had a law degree was working on Wallstreet as an analyst in the Internet sector.  I sought out his advice on my intention to go to business school, and his advice was to attend law school like he did because he believe it was more valuable.  This is exactly what I did and I eventually graduated from law school and became a lawyer in New York City.  Therefter, I regreted taking my brother's advice because I was not happy as a lawyer.<br><br>

          To make a long story short, I did eventually find my work passion.  That passion is technology, innovtion, and solving problems.  I taught myself how to program in PHP and develop web applications especially in the ecommerce space using PHP frameworks such as Magento, the most popular ecommerce framework in the world.  After achieving expert level proficiency in web development and verious programming languages such as PHP, Ruby, C#, amd Java, I wanted to conquer the next new mountain in term of software development.  I was always envious of Jeff Bezos and the new paradigm that Amazon was creating which is the cloud computing.  Again, this technology ignited my burning hunger for the next technology revolution.  This is why I endeaver to make cloud and big data development my next challenge to conquer.  <br><br>

          <br><br>

          Please feel free to drop me an email using the <a href="#contact-me">contact form</a> if you have any questions.
